  "html": "<div class=\"fr-view\"><p><strong>Day 34 - Grammar Tip</strong></p><p>Some of the expressions and the rules of casual speech we explained in the grammar explanation videos may appear also in conversations in 「です・ます」 style.</p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"53.35689045936396%\"><p><br></p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>casual（plain）</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>「です・ます」</p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"53.35689045936396%\"><p>omission of ください in&nbsp;</p><p>「たべてください/たべないでください」</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>〇（obligatory）</p><p><br></p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>△（optional）</p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"53.35689045936396%\"><p>が/けど</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>けど&nbsp;only</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>both</p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"53.35689045936396%\"><p>omission of&nbsp;か&nbsp;with rising intonation</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>〇</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>△</p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"53.35689045936396%\"><p>omission of particles like&nbsp;「を/が」</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>△</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>△</p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"53.35689045936396%\"><p>omission of&nbsp;い&nbsp;in&nbsp;「ている/ています」</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>〇</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>△</p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"53.35689045936396%\"><p>omission of&nbsp;「だ/です」</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>〇</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23.32155477031802%\"><p>&times;</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div>",
